 never before, the scholarly study of race and racism in France. These original essays bring together in one volume new work in history, sociology, anthropology, political science, and legal studies. Each of the eleven articles presents fresh research on the tension between a republican tradition in France that has long denied the legitimacy of acknowledging racial difference and a lived reality in which racial prejudice shaped popular views about foreigners, Jews, immigrants, and colonial people. Several authors also examine efforts to combat racism since the 1970s.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 7aHISTORY / Europe / France.2bisacsh1 aBeriss, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBleich, Erik, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCalvès, Gwénaële, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCamiscioli, Elisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChapman, Herrick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChapman, Herrick, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDewhurst Lewis, Mary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDubois, Laurent, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrader, Laura L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrader, Laura L., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHargreaves, Alec G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLamont, Michèle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLieberman, Robert C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRosenberg, Clifford, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSabbagh